 issues with URLs and links in some or all browsers. To get around this until we have a fix in place, you can disable the &#8216;Use with jQuery&#8217; option. This will not keep the plugin from working, but just eliminates the features for the New Window and No Follow in the Quick Redirects (this was a new feature in ...";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"dfischer";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1216:"<p>Sorry for any issues with the latest plugin upgrade &#8211; in certain installs, the &#8216;use with jQuery&#8217; option is causing some issues with URLs and links in some or all browsers. To get around this until we have a fix in place, you can disable the &#8216;Use with jQuery&#8217; option. This will not keep the plugin from working, but just eliminates the features for the New Window and No Follow in the Quick Redirects (this was a new feature in 5.0).</p>\n<p>To turn off the &#8216;use with jQuery&#8217; feature:</p>\n<ul>\n<li> 1. Go to the plugin settings page &#8211; <strong>Redirect Options</strong>.</li>\n<li> 2. Uncheck the &#8216;Use with jQuery&#8217; feature.</li>\n<li> 3. Save the plugin settings.</li>\n<li> 4. &#8211; if you are using a caching plugin or WP_Cache, clear your cache files.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That should eliminate the issue until we have a fix in place. If it does not, please <a href="mailto:plugins@fischercreativemedia.com" target="_blank">email us</a> a link to your site and what is happening and we will take a look as soon as we can  &#8211; please be sure to include the WP Version and the plugin name.</p>\n<p>Again, sorry for any issues this upgrade may have caused.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base