INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(131, 2, '2013-04-30 06:48:04', '2013-04-30 06:48:04', '<h1>Construction / On-the-Job Accidents</h1>\r\nMost people who are involved in a construction accident or other type of on-the-job accident pursue worker’s compensation benefits to manage health and medical costs. However, if you are injured on the job because of employer negligence or the negligence of someone else, you may be entitled to receive additional compensation. The Law Office of David Azizi has worked with many clients who have successfully filed a negligence claim against their employer and other offending parties. Our team of personal injury lawyers can help you obtain a fair compensation for your specific case. \r\n\r\n<h3>Working with Construction Accident Lawyers </h3>\r\n\r\nConstruction accident lawyers specialize in specific work injuries related to working on a construction project or in the field. Common types of construction accidents include:\r\nCommercial trucking accidents\r\nForklift injuries\r\nOSHA violations\r\nChemical exposure\r\nChemical burns\r\nFalls that cause extensive injury\r\n\r\nIf you are a victim of any of these types of accidents, you may be eligible to receive monetary compensation and benefits beyond worker’s compensation from your employer. \r\n\r\n<h3>Legal Representation for On-the-Job Accidents </h3>\r\n\r\nOn-the-job accidents that result in catastrophic injury or illness will also require formal legal representation from an experienced personal injury attorney. You may need the assistance of personal injury lawyers from AziziPersonalInjyry.com if you are suffering from on-the-job accidents injuries. The common types of on-the-job accident injuries include:\r\nNeurological disorders\r\nSpinal cord injury\r\nBrain injury\r\nAccidental amputation\r\nSevere burns\r\nIllnesses that affect the central nervous system\r\nLoss of movement\r\nCognitive impairment\r\n\r\nAlmost any type of accident can result in short-term and long-term injuries that may require ongoing physician care and other forms of medical care to help an injured client recover from his/her injuries. In many cases, this type of extended care is not covered in a workers’ compensation benefits package so you will need to file an additional claim to receive compensation for all damages incurred. \r\n\r\nOur firm offers a number of services to help you build a strong case for your claim and receive appropriate compensation you deserve. We understand how challenging it can be to work with insurance companies who want a quick settlement so they pay only a fraction of the medical expenses related to your care. At AziziPersonalInjury.com, we take extra steps to protect all of your legal rights and help you receive appropriate compensation. \r\n\r\nWe will not charge you a single dollar until your case is resolved and will do everything legally possible to pursue your case as thoroughly as possible. Contact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so we can provide you immediate assistance in filing your claim or lawsuit.', 'Construction Accidents', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'construction-accidents', '', '', '2013-05-20 21:15:18', '2013-05-20 21:15:18', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/?page_id=131', 0, 'page', '', 0);
