rvices at no cost until we resolve your case, so you don’t have to worry about paying fees until you are satisfied. Contact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so we can learn about your situation and help you receive adequate compensation for the pain and suffering you have endured.', 'Defective Products', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '136-revision', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:50:11', '2013-04-30 06:50:11', '', 136, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/136-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(138, 2, '2013-04-30 06:51:07', '2013-04-30 06:51:07', '<h1>Animal Bites Need Both Medical and Legal Assistance by a Personal Injury Lawyer For Full Recovery</h1>\r\nThousands of people each year, including a high number of children, suffer bites from animals. Most of these are dog bites, and a startling number of them are from pet dogs that have been unleashed by irresponsible owners. When one of these tragic attacks happen, the victim often has the right to sue the owner to receive compensation for the pain and injury the bite caused. \r\n\r\nThe pet''s owner is responsible for making sure his or her pet is controlled at all times. For dogs, this means the dog must be on a leash whenever it is in any public place and can only run free when it is in the owner''s house or fenced-in yard. If the dog is particularly aggressive or dangerous, a muzzle may even be necessary whenever the dog is in public. If the owner fails to control the pet adequately and someone gets bitten, they can be responsible for the injuries and trauma the bite causes. \r\n\r\nThose who have been bitten by any animal first need to have the injury examined by a medical professional who can thoroughly cleanse and treat the wound. Not only does the wound need prompt and proper care, but there is always the possibility that the animal was diseased and passed the disease to the victim. A call to your doctor or emergency personnel should always be your first move, and you should make every effort to identify or locate the animal so that it can be checked for rabies or other diseases. \r\n\r\nAfter the injury has been treated by a medical professional, qualified and experienced legal assistance such as that available by an animal bite personal injury attorney at AziziPersonalInjury.com should be your next step if you wish to receive the highest possible compensation for your pain and suffering. An experienced animal bite personal injury lawyer with our firm can meet with you at no cost or obligation for the initial consultation and discuss your case with you. Although every case is different, we''ve handled many cases of this nature and can give you an excellent idea of what to expect and how much you may be entitled to receive. Since we work on a contingency basis, there’s never any charge for our service until your case is resolved. Our experience gives us an advantage some other firms may not have, and after we review the facts surrounding your case, including the medical evidence, we can determine if you have grounds to file a suit and begin preparing a solid case.', 'Dog Bites and Attacks', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dog-bites-and-attacks', '', '', '2013-05-20 21:17:27', '2013-05-20 21:17:27', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/?page_id=138', 0, 'page', '', 0);
