INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(316, 2, '2013-05-16 15:07:19', '2013-05-16 15:07:19', '<h1>Frequently asked questions</h1>\r\nPersonal injury cases can be complicated and you may have a lot of questions about your individual case. When you are preparing your personal injury claim, you will need to factor in the time lost from work, medical bills, and several other items to ensure you receive the best possible offer from insurance companies. Working with a personal injury lawyer can help you prepare your claim appropriately so you receive adequate compensation and are treated fairly. Below are some common questions that our clients ask; if you have a question that is not answered here, please contact the Law Office of David Azizi for your free, no obligation consultation.\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">What is a personal injury?</span></h2>\r\nAny physical or mental injury caused by someone’s harmful acts or an act of negligence can be classified as a personal injury. Examples of personal injury include:\r\n\r\n• Car, truck and bus accidents\r\n• Motorcycle collision\r\n• Slip and fall accidents\r\n• Home accidents\r\n• Workplace accidents\r\n• Wrongful death\r\n• Defective product accidents\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">How much do you charge for personal injury cases?</span></h2>\r\nWe do not charge any fees unless there is a settlement or until we recover all compensation on your behalf. Contact us as soon as possible so that we can provide you with immediate assistance for your case.\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">Why should I use a personal injury lawyer?</span></h2>\r\nIf you have been injured physically or emotionally, you need the advice and guidance of a personal injury attorney to determine the total amount of compensation for your case. You have a right to receive compensation for someone else’s negligence, misconduct or other harmful acts. A personal injury attorney can help you aggressively pursue your case to recover any and all damages.\r\n\r\nCan I still file a personal injury claim if the accident was partly my fault? Yes. It is common for most accident victims to receive some compensation even if they contributed to the accident. In California, there is a rule of comparative negligence; this means that if you were 25% at fault for the accident, you can still collect 75% of the value for your case. Contact the Law Office of David Azizi so that we can assess your case.\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">Do I need a personal injury lawyer if the insurance company offers a settlement?</span></h2>\r\nIt is in your best interest to consult with a personal injury attorney before accepting any type of settlement. Even if the insurance company is offering an attractive amount in the settlement, you may still be offered the lowest possible amount by the company; contact the Law Office of David Azizi to make sure you are being treated fairly and will be receiving adequate compensation for your particular case.\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">What type of financial compensation can I receive from a personal injury claim?</span></h2>\r\nAny type of physical or mental pain or suffering you have endured can have both short and long-term implications. This means the extent of damages for your personal injury case may include both compensatory (actual) and punitive (criminal) damages. You may be eligible for financial compensation to cover damages such as:\r\n\r\nLoss of enjoyment\r\nEmbarrassment\r\nMental disability\r\nMedical bills\r\nLost wages\r\nPhysical disabilities\r\nProperty damage\r\nOut of pocket expenses\r\nEmotional trauma\r\nPermanent scars\r\nLoss of earning capacity\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">If I want to look up the law myself, how can I do that?</span></h2>\r\nThere are several websites that provide free access to California law and the laws of other states. You can conduct your own research to learn more about your particular situation. However, working with a personal injury attorney that specializes in California cases can help you reach a decision about your next steps much faster.\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">What is the statute of limitation in California for personal injury cases?</span></h2>\r\nFor adults, the personal injury case must be pursued within two years from the date of the injury. You must either settle the case or file a lawsuit to protect the statute of limitations. People under 18 years of age have until their 20th birthday to settle the case or file the lawsuit. Still, there are many exceptions to these rules. If the defendant in your case is a California governmental entity, an uninsured motorist, or if the accident occurred outside of the state of California, the rules and exceptions will vary significantly.\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">If I don’t have health insurance, how can I get medical treatment for my injuries?</span></h2>\r\nThere are several health care providers in California that provide health care services on lien for our clients. They will wait for the final verdict of the case and settlement before getting paid. This is an attractive option for many of our clients, even if they have coverage with an HMO or PPO. Contact the Law Office of David Azizi so that we can assess your specific case.\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">If I have injuries from participating in a sport, can I file a personal injury claim?</span></h2>\r\nIn most cases, you will not be able to file a personal injury claim. The State of California has a rule of law called the ‘assumption of the risk’ which prohibits recovery from the party that caused the injury during a sport-related accident. You should consult with an attorney to determine any provisions or exceptions to this rule.\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">Why should I choose the Law Office of David Azizi to represent my case?</span></h2>\r\nWe specialize in litigating personal injury cases and have extensive experience in handling personal injury cases. We are always up-to-date on the latest rules, regulations and interpretations of California laws. We take pride in our work and are dedicated to helping all of our clients receive the best compensation possible. We understand how challenging it can be to find a suitable personal injury attorney for your claim, but we offer you a free, no obligation consultation so you can learn more about us and allow us to provide immediate assistance with your claim.\r\n<h2><span style="color: #00456a;">If I hire you to represent me, do I have to file reports with my insurance company?</span></h2>\r\nWhen you choose AziziPersonalInjury.com to represent your case, we will handle all of the necessary paperwork and get in touch with your insurance company as needed.', 'FAQs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-7', '', '', '2013-05-16 15:07:19', '2013-05-16 15:07:19', '', 7, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/7-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
