INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(318, 2, '2013-04-30 07:07:26', '2013-04-30 07:07:26', '<h1>Amputation Injury Settlements</h1>\r\n\r\nIf you have suffered injuries from a construction accident, auto accident or any other accident that resulted in amputation or dismemberment, you will need the assistance of an experienced amputation injury lawyer to represent you in your case. The Law Office of David Azizi has extensive experience in the litigation of cases wherein the client has sustained amputation or dismemberment injuries. Amputation accidents can be physically and emotionally devastating as well as leaving you and your family in a state of financial hardship. We specialize in serious personal injury cases and know what it takes litigate cases in order to recover the maximum settlement or verdict possible.\r\n\r\n<h3>When to Pursue an Amputation Injury Lawyer</h3>\r\n\r\nAny type of accident can be a traumatic experience, but when an amputation is required as a result of someone else’s negligence, you have certain rights that can help you recover compensation for damages sustained. The common types of amputation or dismemberment injuries occur when:\r\nYou have lost an arm, leg, hand or foot in an auto accident\r\nYou have lost a limb from a construction accident\r\nYou have lost a limb as a result of negligence on private or public property\r\nYou have had to undergo amputation from malpractive by a surgeon\r\nYou have suffered injuries and a loss of a limb from machines or equipment at work\r\n\r\nAn amputation is a form of a catastrophic personal injury and these cases cannot be taken lightly. At the Law Office of David Azizi, we take the time to conduct a full assessment of your case in order to build a solid claim against the offending party.\r\n\r\n<h3>Working with an Amputation Injury Lawyer</h3>\r\n\r\nWe know how challenging it can be to be responsible for rising medical costs, not being able to return to work or having to manage the emotional repercussions of a traumatic accident. This is why our experienced amputation lawyers will do everything legally possible to investigate your case so that you can receive the compensation you deserve. We will contact witnesses, get in touch with medical professionals and forecast the future costs of managing your medical and healthcare expenses so that we can fight for the appropriate amount of damages for your specific case.\r\n\r\nThe team of legal professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com will not charge you any fees until your case is resolved. We are dedicated to helping you with your claim. Contact us today at (800) 991-LAW2 so that we can provide you with immediate assistance.', 'Amputation Injury', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '110-revision-5', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:07:26', '2013-04-30 07:07:26', '', 110, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/110-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(319, 2, '2013-04-30 07:16:21', '2013-04-30 07:16:21', '<h1>Bicycle and Bike Accidents</h1>\r\nAlmost every Vehicle Code in the country states that bicyclists have the same rights and responsibilities as a driver of a motor vehicle. However, many motorists do not realize how easy it is to run into a bicyclist. Bicycle accidents can occur at any time. The majority of bicycle accidents occur in a bike lane, crosswalk, or when a car or truck makes a turn without checking their blind spot. A bicycle accident or a bicycle-car crash can be serious and you will need the advice of an experienced bicycle accident lawyer from the Law Office of David Azizi. \r\n\r\n<h3>Why Do You Need a Personal Injury Lawyer for a Bicycle Accident?</h3>\r\n\r\nAWhen you have been badly injured as a result of a bicycle accident, you need the assistance of a personal injury lawyer to help you receive the compensation you deserve for damages you have sustained. While some people suffer serious injuries at the scene of the accident, many suffer from ongoing pain and health problems weeks, even months after the bike accident occurred. In all of these cases, a personal injury attorney from the Law Offices of David Azizi can help you receive the appropriate compensation you deserve. \r\n\r\nA bicycle or bike accident can produce serious injuries, and you may need the assistance of an experienced personal injury attorney to receive full compensation for any lost wages, medical expenses and other related costs. The professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com specialize in road accidents case \r\n\r\nYou need the assistance of a strong and experienced attorney to present your case after a bicycle accident, and we will always look out for your best interests.\r\n\r\n<h3>How Azizi Personal Injury Will Manage Your Bike Accident Case</h3>\r\n\r\nOur firm gets involved in building a solid case by reviewing police reports, interviewing witnesses, conducting scene investigations, retaining the appropriate experts, and conducting the necessary discovery. Even though you can manage these tasks on your own, our experienced attorneys can speed up the process and make sure all of the facts surrounding your case are covered. \r\n\r\nContact us as soon as possible so we can take a close look at your case ad to help you get started on a successful recovery. Bicycle and bike accidents can take their toll on your physical and emotional health for several years after the event, so it’s important to work with an experienced personal injury attorney from the Law Offices of David Azizi. ', 'Bicycle and Bike Accidents', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '114-revision-6', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:16:21', '2013-04-30 07:16:21', '', 114, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/114-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(320, 2, '2013-04-30 07:16:08', '2013-04-30 07:16:08', '<h1>Brain Injury Lawyers in Los Angeles and California</h1>\r\nIf you or a family member has suffered from a brain injury as a result of an accident or other catastrophic event, you will need the assistance of an experienced personal injury lawyer from the Law Offices of David Azizi to handle the case. The effects of brain injuries can last for years, even decades, and you may be responsible for expensive medical bills, counseling and other health care cost. AzizPersonalInjuyr.com can help you litigate your brain injury case and ensure that you receive the appropriate compensation for damages which you deserve. \r\n\r\n<h3>Why Work with a Brain Injury Lawyer? </h3>\r\n\r\nDealing with traumatic brain injury can be a complicated process, and most health care providers do not have the resources to cover all of the recovery and rehabilitation costs involved. Victims of a brain injury, their families and/or caregivers need specialized legal representation to assist them in litigating a solid case against the offending negligent party. AziziPersonalInjury.com can help you with every stage of this process, and our lawyers have extensive experience in the field to represent your interest vigorously. \r\n\r\n<h3>What are the Symptoms of Brain Injury? </h3>\r\n\r\nMany symptoms of brain injury do not show up for several weeks or months after the initial accident or event, so it is important to recognize the symptoms as soon as they begin to interfere with day-to-day life activities. When brain functions are disrupted, the individual may experience:\r\nDisturbed sleep patterns\r\nSlowed or impaired thinking\r\nDifficulty concentrating\r\nMemory lapses\r\nFaulty judgement\r\nPeriods of depression\r\n\r\n\r\nIn many cases, the individual will need to undergo cognitive and neurological testing to find out how severe the brain injury is, and what parts of the brain have been damaged. \r\n\r\nAll of these effects and the medical care that the individual needs must be taken on by the patient or their families. This financial burden may be reduced with the help of a personal injury attorney from AzizPersonalInjury.com; our firm will do everything possible to keep the client’s best interests in mind, and do the work necessary to build a solid case. \r\n\r\n<h3>How the Law Office of David Azizi Can Assist You with your Brain Injury Case? </h3>\r\n\r\nAt AziziPersonalInjury.com, we offer a free, no obligation initial consultation. If we accept your case, we will not charge you until the case has been resolved. ', 'Brain Injury Lawyers in Los Angeles and California', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '116-revision-5', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:16:08', '2013-04-30 07:16:08', '', 116, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/116-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(321, 2, '2013-04-30 07:07:51', '2013-04-30 07:07:51', '<h1>Burn, Fire & Explosion Injuries</h1>\r\nIf you have suffered from burn, fire or explosion injuries as a result of an accident, you may be eligible to receive compensation for your damages from the negligent party. Burn injuries that are the result of a fire or explosion can be very serious and require intensive medical care including but not limited to outpatient treatment from physicians, dermatologists and physical rehabilitation centers. The Law Office of David Azizi has extensive experience in handling burn injury cases. \r\n\r\n<h3>Burn Injury Cases </h3>\r\n\r\nNearly 2.4 million burn injuries are reported every year in the United States, and 75,000 of those injuries required hospitalization in the last year. Burn victims not only suffer from the immediate pain but also suffer from many emotional issues as a result of the traumatic experience. A burn injury can be a physically and emotionally devastating experience. These complex cases often require the case to be handled by an experienced personal injury attorney. \r\n\r\nSince there are several factors involved in determining the severity of the burn, determining if the injury was a result of negligence as well as finding out if the burns will create lifelong problems for the individual, you will need an experienced and knowledgeable burn injury lawyer to represent you. The Law Offices of David Azizi will take the time to assess your specific case and determine what the best course of action for your case will be. \r\n\r\n<h3>Fire Injury and Explosion Injury Cases </h3>\r\n\r\nIn addition to sustaining burn injuries from an accident, many people are injured from heat inhalation, systemic toxins in the environment and smoke inhalation. Negligence is the most common reason for fires and explosions. \r\n\r\n<h3>How a Burn Injury Lawyer Can Help You? </h3>\r\n\r\nAn experienced burn injury attorney from AziziPersonalInjury.com can determine the scope of damages sustained by victims of fire and explosion accidents. We understand that in addition to the physical injuries sustained, a burn victim also suffers from depression, mental anguish, post traumatic disorder and embarrassment. \r\n\r\nOur firm will always look out for your best interests and make sure we recover for both your physical and emotional injuries. At AziziPersonalInjury.com, we do not charge you until we recover on your behalf. We are committed to helping you receive compensation from damages from your burn, fire and explosion injury case. Contact us as soon as possible so that we may provide you immediate assistance.', 'Burn, Fire, and Explosion Injuries', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '120-revision-3', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:07:51', '2013-04-30 07:07:51', '', 120, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/120-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(322, 2, '2013-04-30 07:07:56', '2013-04-30 07:07:56', '<h1>Bus Accidents</h1>\r\nIf you have suffered serious injuries after being struck by a bus or been involved in a collision with a bus, you will need legal representation from an experienced personal injury lawyer. The Law Offices of David Azizi has extensive experience in representing clients involved in bus accidents and has helped many clients recover appropriate compensation for their damages. \r\n\r\n<h3>When to Contact a Bus Accident Lawyer </h3>\r\n\r\nA bus accident or crash that involves heavy vehicles can result in serious injuries for all parties involved, and the number of bus-related accidents and injuries continues to rise in high-traffic areas around California. You will need the assistance of an experienced bus accident lawyer if you or a loved one has been involved in any of the following bus accidents including but not limited to:\r\nSchool bus crashes\r\nRiding in a bus that collided with private or public property\r\nNegligent driving by a bus driver\r\nPoor road conditions that caused a bus accident\r\nDangerous weather conditions that resulted in a bus accident\r\nWaalking in a pedestrian crossing and getting struck by a bus\r\nCar and bus collitions\r\n\r\nVictims of bus accidents can suffer extensive injuries including paralysis, burns, head trauma and broken bones. These circumstances often require both short-term and long-term medical care resulting in extensive medical bills, surgery, therapy and other specialized care. \r\n\r\n<h3>Working with a Bus Accident Attorney </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Law Office of David Azizi has provided aggressive and professional legal services to clients in the field of personal injury for many years and helped our clients receive the compensation they deserve. Bus accidents can be a very distressing event and often involve a great deal of physical and emotional pain and suffering. You may be suffering from broken bones, severe muscle and joint pain, or even head injuries as a result of a bus accident. You need the assistance of an experienced bus accident lawyer to help you file the appropriate claims or lawsuit against the offending party and receive the compensation you deserve. \r\n\r\nAziziPersonalInjury.com does not charge any fees for a consultation or services until the case is resolved. We take extra steps to evaluate your case by determining the best course of action for your specific case. We always work with your best interests in mind, and will do what it takes to investigate the accident, interview witnesses and consult with medical professionals as needed. \r\n\r\nContact the Law Office of David Azizi today for a free, no obligation consultation so that we can provide you with immediate assistance.', 'Bus Accidents', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '122-revision-3', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:07:56', '2013-04-30 07:07:56', '', 122, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/122-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(323, 2, '2013-04-30 07:17:10', '2013-04-30 07:17:10', '<h1>Car Accident Claims Settled by AziziPersonalInjury.com</h1>\r\nWell over six million auto accidents occur each year, and every year the number continues to rise. This appalling number includes accidents between two vehicles, those between one vehicle and someone else using the road, and those that involve one vehicle and some object. Worse, over forty thousand people lose their lives each year from car crashes, and nearly every one of these tragic deaths was preventable. \r\n\r\nOver ninety percent of these accidents involve cars or light trucks and also result in nearly three million injuries each year. When you consider the medical costs, the time and wages lost from work, recovery expenses for people and property, it''s clear that an experienced personal injury lawyer should be consulted if you or a loved one has been involved in any accident where he or she was not at fault. \r\n\r\nWhile it may not be your first instinct, having a personal injury lawyer on your side following an auto accident should be second only to quickly receiving proper and prompt medical care for anyone who was injured in the accident. While you may be in shock after an accident, you should try to avoid panicking and the following steps should be taken: \r\n\r\n1)	Determine if anyone was injured and seek professional medical assistance if it is needed. Do not attempt to move any injured persons, but mark the scene of the accident with cones and flares if possible.\r\n2)	Move the vehicles involved to the side of the road if possible, away from traffic that may add to the accident.\r\n3)	Notify the police and wait for them to arrive and conduct an accident investigation.\r\n4)	Get the names and personal information, including insurance, of everyone involved in the accident, including any witnesses or passengers.\r\n5)	In spite of the shock and adrenaline, do not discuss the accident with anyone except the police. \r\n6)	Contact a knowledgeable and experienced personal injury attorney at AziziPersonalInjury.com\r\n\r\nSoon after the accident you can expect to be contacted by insurance companies who will offer a settlement. While this settlement may be in their best interests, it is not always in yours, and you should avoid signing or accepting any proposal until you have consulted with an attorney. The amount you are offered may not cover all your expenses,expenses and one of our attorneys can make sure that you receive full compensation for every cost, now and for the future.\r\n\r\nPlease contact us for a free initial consultation, without any obligation, if you have suffered the loss of a loved one or have been injured in any accident that was not your fault. We can help you get through the maze of insurance issues and make sure that nothing is left out of your settlement, and we never charge until your case is resolved. You need a dedicated personal injury lawyer who knows all the tricks the others will use to get you to sign away your only chance to receive a settlement that''s fair for you, and we''ll make sure your interests are not among your losses.', 'Car Accidents Settled by AziziPersonalInjury.com', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '124-revision-4', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:17:10', '2013-04-30 07:17:10', '', 124, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/124-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(324, 2, '2013-04-30 07:08:05', '2013-04-30 07:08:05', '<h1>Claims Against Public/Government Entities</h1>\r\nIf you are working as a police officer or other government employee, you are bound by certain laws and regulations above and beyond standard employment law. In many cases, you will need to file a ‘notice of claim’ within at least 60 days after the injury. The Law Office of David Azizi offers a number of services for those who need to file claims against public and government entities such as school districts, police stations or city and county offices. If you do not follow certain guidelines or rules that pertain to the federal, state and city government guidelines, you may not have a basis for your case.\r\n\r\nFiling a lawsuit against the government can be a complex process; the Law Office of David Azizi has over ten years of experience representing clients that need assistance in bringing claims against their employer to court. If you have been a victim of discrimination, harassment or wrongfully terminated from your employer, you have certain rights and can file a claim against the offending party.\r\n<h3>Common Claims Against Public or Government Entities</h3>\r\nKnowing when the government or public entity is involved in an injury can be a ‘gray area’ so it’s important to obtain the assistance of a personal injury attorney to help assess the situation.\r\n\r\nNo government entities or offices are immune to the rules and regulations of employment law in the United States, but there are certain reporting laws that employees of these entities must comply with in order to file a legal claim. You may need to bring your case to court if you have experienced any of the following during your course of employment:\r\nSexual harassment\r\nWrongful termination for adhering to mandatory reporting law\r\nRetaliation for filing a report\r\nDiscrimination in promotion\r\nViolations of whistleblower laws\r\nRetaliation for any protected activities\r\n\r\nYou may be entitled to file a claim against a public or government entity for circumstances that involve:\r\nEmployee of a government entity who has been negligent while operating a motor vehicle\r\nWrongful acts by school authorities or employee’s\r\nWrongful acts or omissions of any employee of the Federal Government\r\n\r\nAl cases against the Federal government are controlled by the Federal tort Claims Act and must be brought in the Federal District Court where the plaintiff resides or the injury occurred. There is no right to a jury trial in these cases, and the case will be tried by a judge.\r\n<h3>Procedure Requirements for Government Entity Cases in the State of California</h3>\r\nThe State of California has specific rules and processes in place for those who need to file a lawsuit against a government entity. All claims must be based on facts and explain all injuries sustained and any specific details such as names and agencies of those you feel are responsible for your injury. When you present your claim, the entity has only four choices:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Reject the Claim</li>\r\n	<li>Give notice that the Claim is insufficient</li>\r\n	<li>Do nothing about the Claim</li>\r\n	<li>Approve the Claim</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Working with a Government Entity Lawyer</h3>\r\nThe professional legal team at the Law Office of David Azizi has several years of experience in managing government employee, law enforcement officer and teacher cases and we are dedicated to providing you with fair legal representation. We do everything legally possible to investigate your case and make sure we have enough details and evidence available so that you can file your claim.\r\n\r\nWith several years of experience in the field, we are very knowledgeable about the employment laws and employee protection laws that govern the state of California. Whether you’re a school district employee, a police officer or a government official that has been discriminated against or harassed, working with a qualified government entity lawyer can help you get your case resolved and may also result in compensation of damages.\r\n\r\nAziziPersonalInjury.com does not charge clients any fees until the case is resolved, so you don’t have to worry about the process of filing your claim until you are satisfied with the outcome. You deserve to receive fair and adequate compensation for any hardship you have endured because of somebody else’s negligence of mandatory rules, laws and regulations.\r\n\r\nContact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so that we can assess your situation.', 'Claims Against Public/Government Entities', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '126-revision-6', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:08:05', '2013-04-30 07:08:05', '', 126, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/126-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(325, 2, '2013-04-30 07:08:11', '2013-04-30 07:08:11', '<h1>Construction / On-the-Job Accidents</h1>\r\nMost people who are involved in a construction accident or other type of on-the-job accident pursue worker’s compensation benefits to manage health and medical costs. However, if you are injured on the job because of employer negligence or the negligence of someone else, you may be entitled to receive additional compensation. The Law Office of David Azizi has worked with many clients who have successfully filed a negligence claim against their employer and other offending parties. Our team of personal injury lawyers can help you obtain a fair compensation for your specific case. \r\n\r\n<h3>Working with Construction Accident Lawyers </h3>\r\n\r\nConstruction accident lawyers specialize in specific work injuries related to working on a construction project or in the field. Common types of construction accidents include:\r\nCommercial trucking accidents\r\nForklift injuries\r\nOSHA violations\r\nChemical exposure\r\nChemical burns\r\nFalls that cause extensive injury\r\n\r\nIf you are a victim of any of these types of accidents, you may be eligible to receive monetary compensation and benefits beyond worker’s compensation from your employer. \r\n\r\n<h3>Legal Representation for On-the-Job Accidents </h3>\r\n\r\nOn-the-job accidents that result in catastrophic injury or illness will also require formal legal representation from an experienced personal injury attorney. You may need the assistance of personal injury lawyers from AziziPersonalInjyry.com if you are suffering from on-the-job accidents injuries. The common types of on-the-job accident injuries include:\r\nNeurological disorders\r\nSpinal cord injury\r\nBrain injury\r\nAccidental amputation\r\nSevere burns\r\nIllnesses that affect the central nervous system\r\nLoss of movement\r\nCognitive impairment\r\n\r\nAlmost any type of accident can result in short-term and long-term injuries that may require ongoing physician care and other forms of medical care to help an injured client recover from his/her injuries. In many cases, this type of extended care is not covered in a workers’ compensation benefits package so you will need to file an additional claim to receive compensation for all damages incurred. \r\n\r\nOur firm offers a number of services to help you build a strong case for your claim and receive appropriate compensation you deserve. We understand how challenging it can be to work with insurance companies who want a quick settlement so they pay only a fraction of the medical expenses related to your care. At AziziPersonalInjury.com, we take extra steps to protect all of your legal rights and help you receive appropriate compensation. \r\n\r\nWe will not charge you a single dollar until your case is resolved and will do everything legally possible to pursue your case as thoroughly as possible. Contact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so we can provide you immediate assistance in filing your claim or lawsuit.', 'Construction Accidents', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '131-revision-5', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:08:11', '2013-04-30 07:08:11', '', 131, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/131-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
