INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(327, 2, '2013-04-30 07:08:24', '2013-04-30 07:08:24', '<h1>Defective Road Design or Dangerous Roads</h1>\r\nDangerous road conditions, poorly constructed highways and defective road design can lead to an accident that leaves you seriously injured. The Law Office of David Azizi has extensive experience in representing clients who have suffered injuries as a result of a defective road design and/or dangerous roads, and will do everything possible to help you receive the compensation for you deserve your damages. \r\n\r\n<h3>Reasons to Contact a Defective Road Design or Dangerous Roads Lawyer </h3>\r\n\r\nWhen you have suffered physical or emotional trauma as a direct result of defective or dangerous road, you will need the assistance of an experienced attorney to handle the case. You may need legal representation from the lawyers at AziziPersonalInjury.com. The common types of defective or dangerous road condition accident include:\r\nFailure of bridges or overhead structures\r\nDangerous or unmarked railroad crossings\r\nPoorly marked construction zones\r\nWeak or poorly marked shoulders on the highway\r\nInadequate lighting on highways or roads\r\nPOtholes, cracks or debris on pavements or highway roads\r\nMissing traffic signals\r\nMissing road signs\r\nImproperly installed road signs\r\nMissing guard rail\r\nMissing median barrier\r\n\r\nIn the state of California, certain rules, regulations and time limitations apply when pursuing a claim against civil or government entities. It is very important to work with an experienced attorney from the Law Offices of David Azizi who can approach the case with all of these rules in mind. \r\n\r\n<h3>Working with a Defective Road Design Attorney </h3>\r\n\r\nIf you have been injured as a result of a defective road design or dangerous road condition, the professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com are committed to helping you pursue your case vigorously so that you can recover the appropriate compensation for all damages incurred. Many motorists do not realize that there are several sources of compensation beyond the insurance companies. In many defective road design and/or dangerous road cases, the injured party can take action against the appropriate government agency such as Cal Trans, or any other transportation agencies, as well as other local or state highway commission. \r\n\r\nIf you have been a victim of defective road design or suffered injuries on dangerous roads, get in touch with our legal team so we can conduct an assessment of your claim. We do not require any payment upfront or charge you fees until the case has been resolved; this means you can count on fair legal representation. \r\n\r\nContact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so that we can start learning about the incident and help you file the right claims or lawsuit and get you the compensation you deserve.', 'Defective and Dangerous Roads', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '134-revision-3', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:08:24', '2013-04-30 07:08:24', '', 134, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/134-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(328, 2, '2013-04-30 07:08:32', '2013-04-30 07:08:32', '<h1>Defective Products</h1>\r\nAny product that causes physical injury or illness can be defined as a defective product. When the manufacturer has failed to label its product with the list of hazards and risks involved, consumers who sustain injuries from using the product can file a lawsuit and claims to receive compensation for damages. \r\n\r\nAnybody can be a victim of injury from defective products and the costs of medical expenses related to emergency care and rehabilitation can be a source of financial burden and stress for the individual and their families. Filing a claim or lawsuit are the first essential steps for receiving compensation for damages that result from defective products. \r\n\r\nProducts liability laws fall under Tort Law under the same category of always a personal injury cases. You will need to work with an experienced personal injury or defective product lawyer from AziziPersonalInjury.com who can assess your situation and determine which type of claim or lawsuit you need to file. What are the Different Types of Product Defects? A Defective Product is when a manufacturer makes the product available to the general public with defects and these defects cause an injury. \r\n\r\nThe different kinds of defective product cases include:\r\nDesign defects – when a manufacturer fails to address certain safety precautions and there are problems inherent in the product’s design\r\nManufacturing defects – negligence of safety protocol or parts that are not properly installed may result in the breakdown of the product. This may also include tainted food.\r\nMarketing defects – improper labeling or not issuing appropriate warnings about products that may be dangerous to the consumer. This may also include neglecting to include warnings in an instruction manual or guide.\r\n\r\nDefective product lawyers have the technical and scientific expertise needed to help you file the right claims, conduct necessary research about manufacturers and companies, and build a solid case against the offending party. \r\n\r\n<h3>Warranties and the Defective Product </h3>\r\n\r\nIf there are warranties involved with your situation, you may be eligible for additional compensation. A warranty is a guarantee on the product you purchased and may be an ‘implied’ product warranty or an ‘express’ product warranty. \r\n\r\nAn implied warranty is one that is not written or spoken but does guarantee that the product will be function as it is supposed to function. For example, if you purchased a cell phone from a phone dealer, you expect the speakers to work without the dealer explaining that they will work because the speakers are a necessary component of all cell phones. \r\n\r\nAn express warranty is one that makes a statement about the fact of the product, provides a description of the product, or one in which the buyer has been shown a demo or model of the product before purchasing a replica of the item. \r\n\r\nIt’s important to understand that if there are any disclaimers involved, you may not have a case. A disclaimer is any statement made by the dealer that specifies any defects or potential problems with the product. If you purchased a product and experienced a problem even with the disclaimer, you may not be entitled to compensation from any injuries sustained. \r\n\r\n<h3>Working with a Defective Product Attorney </h3>\r\n\r\nA personal injury lawyer that specializes in defective products and product liability can help you protect your rights and receive appropriate compensation for damages. If you’ve been injured or become ill after using a certain product, contact the professionals at AziziPerosnalInjury.com so that we can assess your situation and help you build your case. \r\n\r\nOur firm is dedicated to providing you with the best services possible and will conduct all necessary research, interview company contacts and contact medical professionals to help you build your case. We provide you with services at no cost until we resolve your case, so you don’t have to worry about paying fees until you are satisfied. Contact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so we can learn about your situation and help you receive adequate compensation for the pain and suffering you have endured.', 'Defective Products', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '136-revision-3', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:08:32', '2013-04-30 07:08:32', '', 136, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/136-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(329, 2, '2013-04-30 07:08:37', '2013-04-30 07:08:37', '<h1>Animal Bites Need Both Medical and Legal Assistance by a Personal Injury Lawyer For Full Recovery</h1>\r\nThousands of people each year, including a high number of children, suffer bites from animals. Most of these are dog bites, and a startling number of them are from pet dogs that have been unleashed by irresponsible owners. When one of these tragic attacks happen, the victim often has the right to sue the owner to receive compensation for the pain and injury the bite caused. \r\n\r\nThe pet''s owner is responsible for making sure his or her pet is controlled at all times. For dogs, this means the dog must be on a leash whenever it is in any public place and can only run free when it is in the owner''s house or fenced-in yard. If the dog is particularly aggressive or dangerous, a muzzle may even be necessary whenever the dog is in public. If the owner fails to control the pet adequately and someone gets bitten, they can be responsible for the injuries and trauma the bite causes. \r\n\r\nThose who have been bitten by any animal first need to have the injury examined by a medical professional who can thoroughly cleanse and treat the wound. Not only does the wound need prompt and proper care, but there is always the possibility that the animal was diseased and passed the disease to the victim. A call to your doctor or emergency personnel should always be your first move, and you should make every effort to identify or locate the animal so that it can be checked for rabies or other diseases. \r\n\r\nAfter the injury has been treated by a medical professional, qualified and experienced legal assistance such as that available by an animal bite personal injury attorney at AziziPersonalInjury.com should be your next step if you wish to receive the highest possible compensation for your pain and suffering. An experienced animal bite personal injury lawyer with our firm can meet with you at no cost or obligation for the initial consultation and discuss your case with you. Although every case is different, we''ve handled many cases of this nature and can give you an excellent idea of what to expect and how much you may be entitled to receive. Since we work on a contingency basis, there’s never any charge for our service until your case is resolved. Our experience gives us an advantage some other firms may not have, and after we review the facts surrounding your case, including the medical evidence, we can determine if you have grounds to file a suit and begin preparing a solid case.', 'Dog Bites and Attacks', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '138-revision-3', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:08:37', '2013-04-30 07:08:37', '', 138, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/138-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(330, 2, '2013-04-30 07:08:42', '2013-04-30 07:08:42', '<h1>Electrocution Accidents</h1>\r\nIf you have been injured or lost a loved one due to an electrocution accident, you may be a good candidate for filing a wrongful death or personal injury claim against the offending party. The Law Office of David Azizi specializes in electrocution accidents and construction-related incidents. \r\n\r\n<h3>Identifying Electrocution Accidents </h3>\r\n\r\nElectrocution accidents can occur from a variety of circumstances. Whatever the case may be, electrocution injuries can result in paralysis, severe burns and other types of physical trauma that leaves the victim handicapped and requiring extensive medical attention. \r\n\r\nElectrocution accidents can result from:\r\nExcessive or unmonitored voltage levels\r\nFaulty circuit boards and power lines\r\nPoorly marked construction zones or sites\r\nEmployer negligence\r\nInadequate tools and equipment\r\nHeavy machinery with live wires\r\nFaulty machinery and wiring\r\n\r\nElectric shock can have both a physical and psychological effect on its victims, and in some cases, may result in severe heart or brain damage. Working with an experienced electrocution injury attorney means you or family members can receive monetary compensation for damages incurred and/or reprimand the offending party with additional fines and fees. \r\n\r\n<h3>Working with an Electrocution Injury Lawyer </h3>\r\n\r\nThe legal professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com understand the serious physical and mental injuries that can occur as a result of electric shock and electrocution. Most victims suffer from extensive physical pain immediately after the accident, but may also suffer in the form of lost wages, the inability to continue work, and lifelong impairments when performing day-to-day tasks. Filing the appropriate claims or lawsuit for compensation is important for the victim and their families, allowing them to receive the compensation they deserve. \r\n\r\nAt the Law Office of David Azizi, we take all of our personal injury cases very seriously. We will do everything possible to investigate your case so that we have accurate and relevant information prepared to file a claim or lawsuit. From interviewing witnesses to compiling information from medical professionals, we have the resources and expertise to put together a strong case on your behalf. We will not charge you any fees until the case is resolved, so you can count on our experience and professional services until we arrive at a favorable outcome. Contact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so we provide you with immediate assistance.', 'Electrocution Accidents', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '140-revision-3', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:08:42', '2013-04-30 07:08:42', '', 140, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/140-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(331, 2, '2013-04-30 07:08:52', '2013-04-30 07:08:52', '<h1>A Motorcycle Accident Personal Injury Lawyer Can Help You Recover.</h1>\r\nA motorcycle accident can be particularly serious, and you may need both medical care and a motorcycle accident personal injury attorney to get everything back together. Although any motor vehicle accident can cause an injury, those that involve a motorcycle are often much worse and can produce crippling results. The motorcyclist is not usually the one at fault in a motorcycle accident, but not seeing him or her is no excuse for the negligent driver of the other vehicle. \r\n\r\nA motorcycle accident often produces very serious injuries, or even death, and without a personal injury lawyer from AziziPersonalInjury.com, you may not receive full compensation for all your medical expenses, lost wages during your recovery time or beyond, or for less obvious costs such as therapy or even fully restoring your bike. Your distress and pain, while not physical, need to be addressed as well, and this requires a strong and determined attorney to present your case. \r\n\r\nPrompt medical care should always be your first concern after any motorcycle accident. Serious injuries or unconsciousness, however, may prevent you from being able to take the following necessary steps: \r\n\r\n1)	Remain at the scene of the accident until the police have arrived.\r\n2)	File or assist in the preparation of a police report.\r\n3)	Obtain medical care.\r\n4)	Obtain the license number, name, and personal information on everyone involved in the accident.\r\n5)	Obtain the names of witnesses to the accident.\r\n6)	Seek prompt legal assistance.\r\n\r\nIf you''ve been badly injured, your personal injury lawyer can help with interviewing witnesses, reviewing the police reports, and discussing possible settlements with insurance companies while you recover. You may not be able to do these on your own, and others may be pressing you to take a quick settlement that is not in your best interests.\r\n\r\n<h3>A personal injury attorney with our firm will look out for your best interests, both immediate and for the future.</h3>\r\n\r\nIf you are the survivor of someone who''s been sadly lost to a motorcycle accident, an experienced attorney from AziziPersonalInjury.com can evaluate the facts surrounding the accident and work with you to make sure that you receive full compensation for medical expenses, loss of income, and your pain and suffering. We are always willing to meet with you for a free, no obligation, initial compensation, and our familiarity with cases of this type will prove to be a solid and welcome help during this traumatic time, and we never charge until your case is resolved..\r\n\r\nPlease contact us as soon as possible so that we can begin helping you deal with the accident and help you begin recovering your life. You only have one chance to settle this matter with those responsible for the motorcycle accident, and we want you to receive the best possible result.', 'Motorcycle Accidents', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '142-revision-3', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:08:52', '2013-04-30 07:08:52', '', 142, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/142-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
